DL>You can 'break' lockup by rebooting your computer.  It doesn't lock 
DL>on startup.  Also if you need to change your password, bring up the
DL>desktop menu (right mouse on desktop), click the arrow next to open,
DL>open settings, select lockup (near the bottom), and then click the
DL>right arrow until you get to the third page.  You can then change the
DL>password. 

OS/2 2.1 supports password lock on startup!

